<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06105078 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06105078 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  COMPUTER; PROGRAM  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Shareware programs are available from computer bulletin boards, computer clubsand from this column. Users try them, then pay a fee to register them if theydecide to use them regularly.;    PRISM -- Want to trace your ancestors andbuild a family tree? Prism is a genealogical data base that will help youplant, nurture and harvest your family tree. A series of menus, help screensand the use of function keys on an International Business Machines Corp. orcompatible computer will have you entering everything you know about yourfamily quickly.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Computing  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  HOW TO TRACE FAMILY TREE, LOCATE LOST ORHIDDEN FILES  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  SharewareTrial copies of these programs are available for $4 each. Send a check toShareware, P.O. Box 4101, Lakewood, Calif. 90711. Please indicate 5 1/4- or 31/2-inch disk.  </MEMO><TEXT>     Once you've entered enough data, you can view or print your family tree,culled from the thousands of names you input. Then, when you want to findabout more about Uncle Max, who homesteaded near Devils Lake, N.D., back atthe turn of the century, you simply search for Max.;    You'll need a harddisk and 640 kilobytes of random-access memory to run Prism. A free versioncan be found on computer bulletin boards. It's limited to 50 people but willgive you a good idea how the program works. The full-blown version costs $44and can be ordered from Gary R. Austin, 1459 Tenth St., Grand Rapids, Mich.49504. Austin also will send you the limited bulletin board version for $5, tocover shipping.;    PROFESSIONAL MASTER KEY -- If accidentally formatting yourhard disk is a recurring nightmare, get yourself a backup program, such asBackup, and use a utility such as PMK that will bring back those files. Asidefrom its unformat features, PMK also will show you a directory of any kind ofhard or floppy disk, unerase files, find files using wild cards, sort files,delete files, rename them and even let you edit text files with a text editorcalled Tiny Edit. If security is a concern, PMK will erase all data from ahard or floppy disk or erase all data from a particular file.;    If PMKsounds like it's a cross between Xtree and the Norton Utilities, twocommercial utilities, it is similar, but, as with most shareware programs, itcosts a lot less. If you're downloading PMK from a bulletin board, look forVersion 3.2. To register, send $35 to Public Brand Software, P.O. Box 51315,Indianapolis, Ind. 46251.;    HOME INSURANCE -- There are a lot of goodreasons for taking inventory of your worldly possessions, not the least ofwhich are the possibilities of theft or fire. This shareware program takes youby the hand on a tour through your home. As you catalog your possessions,you'll be prompted for serial numbers, descriptions and replacement costs,among other details.;    The folks at Homecraft Software recommend that youtake a day for this task. It's a day well spent because insurance companieslike to have the cold, hard facts when you're faced with a loss. This programalso lets you figure out how much insurance you need, and it lets you groupspecial items that may require additional insurance. Then you can printreports and make some intelligent decisions about how much insurance youneed.;    To register for Home Insurance, send $62.95 to Steve Hudgik,Homecraft Computer Products, P.O. Box 974, Tualatin, Ore. 97062.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  NOAH MATTHEWS, Knight-Ridder News Service  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910414  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  563  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday April 14, 199100105078,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury Ne